stateDiagram-v2
    %% The unified seven Linear-canonical states: five active, two inert terminals.
    %% Five active states pass in order; Canceled and Duplicate are inert terminals
    %% reachable from any active state, exactly like Backlog.

    %% Display name carries the spaces of the Linear-canonical "In Progress" state
    %% while the identifier stays space-free for valid transition syntax;
    %% "In Review" gets its display name on the composite declaration below.
    state "In Progress" as InProgress

    [*] --> Backlog

    %% --- The four file-anchored forward transitions ---
    %% readiness gate: proposal.md committed (brainstorm.md alone keeps the unit in Backlog).
    Backlog --> Todo: readiness gate / proposal.md committed

    %% apply gate fires at the Todo to In Progress boundary, which is also where the
    %% human picks the per-issue execution mode. The mode fork is the same apply gate
    %% regardless of mode; all three modes converge on In Review.
    state mode_fork <<choice>>
    Todo --> mode_fork: apply gate / first tasks.md "- [x]"
    note right of mode_fork
        Execution-mode fork (human picks per-issue,
        no automatic Linear-label selection):
        AFK / HIL / Manual all converge on In Review.
    end note
    mode_fork --> InProgress: AFK
    mode_fork --> InProgress: HIL
    mode_fork --> InProgress: Manual

    %% In-Review gate: verify.md created for the in-progress change.
    InProgress --> InReview: In-Review gate / verify.md created

    %% In Review decomposes into two ordered human-steered sub-gates;
    %% joint approval precedes the archive gate. Done is never reached before archive.
    state "In Review" as InReview {
        [*] --> roborev
        roborev --> documenter: approved
        documenter --> [*]: passes
        note right of roborev
            Two ordered human-steered sub-gates:
            roborev (code review) runs first,
            then documenter (docs/handbook review).
            Joint approval precedes archive.
        end note
    }

    %% archive gate: openspec archive succeeds (the sole anchor that fires Done).
    InReview --> Done: archive gate / openspec archive succeeds

    %% --- The shared re-queue ---
    %% A roborev or documenter rejection, or a verify.md "(fail) FAIL" Overall Decision,
    %% re-queues into In Progress above the mode fork so the unit re-selects its mode.
    InReview --> InProgress: re-queue / sub-gate rejection or verify.md "(fail) FAIL"
    note left of InProgress
        Bounded-retries policy (recommended default 3):
        a review-round counter increments once per re-queue
        and resets on archive; on exhaustion the board escalates
        to the human PM layer and stops firing automatic re-queues.
    end note

    Done --> [*]

    %% --- Inert terminals, reachable from any active state ---
    Backlog --> Canceled: abandoned (directory removed without archive)
    Todo --> Canceled: abandoned
    InProgress --> Canceled: abandoned
    InReview --> Canceled: abandoned

    Backlog --> Duplicate: superseded by another change
    Todo --> Duplicate: superseded
    InProgress --> Duplicate: superseded
    InReview --> Duplicate: superseded

    Canceled --> [*]
    Duplicate --> [*]
